    "causal_summary": "Live testing of the code-graph (after F-002/F-003/F-018/F-019 remediation landed) showed that broad-scope scans (`agents+commands+specs+plugins=all`) crash the tree-sitter parser with `memory access out of bounds` on roughly 1,640 of 9,349 candidate files (~17.5%). Skills-only scope is parser-clean. Crashes happen on valid TypeScript files, including test files and runtime modules. The F-003 preservation guard prevents data loss, but parsed coverage is incomplete and the failure is loud enough to obscure real signal.",
